The Essex Arabic Summaries Corpus (EASC) uses copyright material.
Users of the corpus are responsible for ensuring that they comply with
the terms of the copyrights that apply to the source material and the
derived works (summaries) and the terms of relevant copyright law.

1. The Alwatan articles are taken from the newspaper "Alwatan"
   (http://www.alwatan.com.sa/). These articles, and their summaries
   are distributed with permission.

2. The Alrai articles are taken from the newspaper "Alrai"
   (http://www.alrai.com/). These articles, and their summaries
   are distributed with permission.

3. All other articles in the corpus are taken from Wikipedia
   (www.wikipedia.org). They, and their summaries, are distributed
   under the Creative Commons Attributive/Share Alike licence
   (CC-BY-SA) (http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/). The
   original unaltered articles are also available from Wikipedia under
   the the GNU Free Documentation License (unversioned, with no
   invariant sections, front-cover texts, or back-cover texts)
   (http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/fdl.html).  More details on the
   attributive requirements are available from Wikipedia
   (http://wikimediafoundation.org/wiki/Terms_of_Use).

4. Any other original data that is distributed with this corpus is
   made available under the Creative Commons Attributive/Share Alike
   licence (http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/).  You must
   provide details of the source of the material when using it.



